<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1168329467336">
<term>escape velocity</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1168329122893">initial velocity an object needs to escape the gravitational pull of another; it is more accurately defined as the velocity of an object with zero total mechanical energy</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1168329170364">
<term>gravitationally bound</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1168326839699">two object are gravitationally bound if their orbits are closed; gravitationally bound systems have a negative total mechanical energy</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
